1 + \tan x - \sqrt{2} \tan 2x = 0
\end{align*}
We can now factorize the left-hand side and further simplify the equation. 
\begin{align*}
\left( \frac{1 - \sqrt{2} \tan 2x}{\cos x} \right) = \tan x
\end{align*}
When reeday it can be noticed that we have 
