&=\frac{5}{16}+\frac{5}{8}\cos2\theta+\frac{5}{16}\cos^22\theta.\enus{align*}
Combining everything, we have 
\begin{align*}
\cos^5 \theta&=(\cos \theta)(\cos^4 \theta)\\
&=\cos \theta(\frac{5}{16}+\frac{5}{8}\cos2\theta+\frac{5}{16}\cos^22\theta)\\
&=\cos \theta\frac{5}{16}+\cos \theta\frac{5}{8}\cos2\theta+\cos \theta\frac{5}{16}\cos^22\theta
\end{align*}
We can express $\cos^5 \theta$ in a form involving $\cos$ $2\theta$ by using the expression $\cos2\theta=\left(\cos\theta\right)^2-\left(\sin\theta\right)^2.$ This yields
\begin{align*}
